      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an impartial arena judge evaluating two competing startup pitches. Score each using the rubric below and declare a winner.\n\nRubric (must sum to 100):\n- market (0-25): Is the market large, urgent, and willing to pay?\n- originality (0-20): Is this idea novel with no dominant incumbent?\n- feasibility (0-20): Can this realistically be built in 6 months on $25k?\n- differentiation (0-20): Does it have a clear unfair advantage or moat?\n- distribution (0-15): Is there a clear, realistic first channel and distribution path?\n\nTeam A Packet:\n{{ JSON.stringify($input.all()[0].json) }}\n\nTeam B Packet:\n{{ JSON.stringify($input.all()[1].json) }}\n\nReturn ONLY a JSON object with fields:\n- teamAScore (integer 0-100)\n- teamBScore (integer 0-100)\n- teamARubric: { market, originality, feasibility, differentiation, distribution }\n- teamBRubric: { market, originality, feasibility, differentiation, distribution }\n- winner (\"A\" or \"B\")\n- winningConcept (the full concept object of the winner — copy from the winning team packet's concept field)\n- justification (string — explain the scoring delta between the two teams, referencing specific rubric dimensions)\n\nNo markdown. No explanation. Just the JSON object."
